Additional Clauses for Independent Developer EULA

10. Modifications and Customizations
    You are not permitted to modify, adapt, or create derivative works of the Software without explicit permission from the Licensor.
    If you make changes to the Software, such changes will remain the property of the Licensor unless otherwise agreed.
    Any modifications made to the Software by the Licensee are done at their own risk and without liability for the Licensor.

11. User Contributions
    If you allow users to contribute to the development of the Software (e.g., through open-source contributions or feedback), you may include a clause stating that all contributions made to the Software become the exclusive property of the Licensor.
    By submitting any contributions, you grant the Licensor a perpetual, royalty-free, and worldwide license to use, modify, and incorporate those contributions into the Software.
    Example:

"Any code, feedback, or contributions submitted by the Licensee to the Licensor shall become the sole property of the Licensor, and the Licensee waives any rights or claims to those contributions."

12. Attribution and Branding
    If your Software is used publicly (e.g., in apps, websites, or other projects), you may require the Licensee to provide attribution to you as the developer.
    This can include displaying your name or a reference to your company or project.
    Example:

"If the Software is used in a public project, the Licensee agrees to provide appropriate credit to the Licensor, including a visible acknowledgment of the Licensor's contribution in the form of "e-commerce-module" and the Licensor’s website."

13. Third-Party Software and Libraries
    If your Software uses or incorporates third-party software or libraries, you can outline these dependencies and clarify any obligations regarding them.
    You might also want to provide a disclaimer for the use of third-party software.
    Example:

"The Software may contain or use third-party software or libraries. The Licensee agrees to comply with the terms of any applicable third-party licenses."

14. Use in Commercial Projects
    If the Software is intended for both personal and commercial use, clearly define whether and how the Software can be used in commercial environments.
    You can include an additional clause for commercial licenses if you want to restrict the use of the Software to non-commercial purposes unless a separate agreement is made.
    Example:

"The Software may be used for commercial purposes only under a separate commercial license agreement. By default, this license applies to personal or internal non-commercial use."

15. Beta Testing and Early Access
    If your Software is in beta or early access, you can include a clause that limits the user’s rights and clarifies that the Software may have bugs or incomplete features.
    You can also include a clause that requests feedback from the user.
    Example:

"The Software is provided as a beta release and may contain bugs or incomplete features. The Licensee agrees to provide feedback to the Licensor regarding their use of the Software."

16. Software Maintenance and Support
    Define the terms under which you will provide support or maintenance, if any.
    You can specify whether support is available on a paid basis, if it’s limited, or if the software is provided “as-is” with no obligation for maintenance.
    Example:

"The Licensor provides support for the Software at their discretion. Support may be limited and available on a paid basis."

17. Confidentiality
    If the Software contains proprietary information, you may want to include a confidentiality clause to prevent the Licensee from disclosing the details of the Software.
    Example:

"The Licensee agrees not to disclose any confidential or proprietary information related to the Software, including its features, code, and design, to third parties."

18. Data Collection and Usage
    If your Software collects data from the user, you should clarify what data is collected, how it will be used, and if it will be shared with third parties.
    If necessary, link to a full Privacy Policy.
    Example:

"The Software may collect usage data and personal information as described in the Privacy Policy. By using the Software, the Licensee consents to the collection and processing of this data."

19. Indemnification
    This clause protects you from liability in case the Software causes damage or harm to the Licensee or any third party.
    Example:

"The Licensee agrees to indemnify and hold harmless the Licensor from any and all claims, damages, liabilities, and expenses arising out of their use of the Software."

20. Force Majeure
    A force majeure clause releases you from liability if an unforeseen event prevents you from fulfilling your obligations under the agreement (e.g., natural disasters, pandemics, etc.).
    Example:

"The Licensor shall not be held liable for any failure to perform under this Agreement caused by events beyond their reasonable control, including but not limited to acts of God, natural disasters, or technical failures."
